          <ul>
            <li>For this choice of 3 characters, each player needs to define a primary character (that will be played the first match) and two secondary characters (that will be played the second and third match if any).</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            For example, for a total of 100 points, player 1 could select Eiki, Lunasa and Sakuya (40+31+29). Player 2 could select Marisa, Merlin and Cirno (44+31+25). The primaries could be Eiki and Marisa, but not necessarily!
            In that case however, the first match would be Eiki vs Marisa. If player 2 wins, then they choose for the second match their secondary, here Merlin. Player 1 then can counterpick with Lunasa or Sakuya.
            Let's say they select Lunasa here, and win. In such a case, the third match would have to be Sakuya vs Cirno.
          </p>
